## IoT-Stream: A Lightweight Ontology for Internet of Things Data Streams and Its Use with Data Analytics and Event Detection Services

](/paper/IoT-Stream%3A-A-Lightweight-Ontology-for-Internet-of-Elsaleh-Enshaeifar/4c315faa04ca66d11da574cb7d642f1e2931f438)

[Tarek Elsaleh](/author/Tarek-Elsaleh/3122895)[Shirin Enshaeifar](/author/Shirin-Enshaeifar/2395182)[Roonak Rezvani](/author/Roonak-Rezvani/70864492)[Sahr Thomas Acton](/author/Sahr-Thomas-Acton/39229898)[Valentinas Janeiko](/author/Valentinas-Janeiko/1492100767)[M. Bermúdez-Edo](/author/M.-Berm%C3%BAdez-Edo/1401372559)

Computer Science, Engineering

-   1 February 2020

This work presents a light model to semantically annotate streams, IoT-Stream, which takes advantage of common knowledge sharing of the semantics, but keeping the inferences and queries simple, and presents tools that could be used in conjunction to the IoT- Stream model and facilitate the use of semantics in IoT.

## A New Pattern Representation Method for Time-Series Data

](/paper/A-New-Pattern-Representation-Method-for-Time-Series-Rezvani-Barnaghi/bf0736eb83c4476891db4d6b70b41ddd87509f2c)

[Roonak Rezvani](/author/Roonak-Rezvani/70864492)[P. Barnaghi](/author/P.-Barnaghi/1740880)[Shirin Enshaeifar](/author/Shirin-Enshaeifar/2395182)

Computer Science, Engineering

-   1 July 2021

A pattern representation method which represents time-series frames as vectors by first applying Piecewise Aggregate Approximation (PAA) and then applying Lagrangian Multipliers is proposed and a new change point detection method is introduced which uses the constructed patterns in its analysis.

## IoTCrawler: Challenges and Solutions for Searching the Internet of Things

](/paper/IoTCrawler%3A-Challenges-and-Solutions-for-Searching-Iggena-Ilyas/5b99bb0dbc1aea860f56ece6ef5b8b902ee8fcc8)

[Thorben Iggena](/author/Thorben-Iggena/3377197)[Eushay Bin Ilyas](/author/Eushay-Bin-Ilyas/2052007361) [Sebastian Holmgård Christophersen](/author/Sebastian-Holmg%C3%A5rd-Christophersen/2052006252)

Computer Science, Engineering

-   24 February 2021

The IoTCrawler framework is not only another IoT framework, it is a system of systems which connects existing solutions to offer interoperability and to overcome data fragmentation, offering solutions for crawling, indexing and searching IoT data sources, while ensuring privacy and security, adaptivity and reliability.

## Semi-supervised Learning for Identifying the Likelihood of Agitation in People with Dementia

](/paper/Semi-supervised-Learning-for-Identifying-the-of-in-Rezvani-Kouchaki/0c713605983e1aeb7766fba2aed176d29cbdab37)

[Roonak Rezvani](/author/Roonak-Rezvani/70864492)[S. Kouchaki](/author/S.-Kouchaki/2481031)[R. Nilforooshan](/author/R.-Nilforooshan/5195508)[D. Sharp](/author/D.-Sharp/1879253179)[P. Barnaghi](/author/P.-Barnaghi/1740880)

Medicine, Computer Science

-   14 May 2021

A semi-supervised model which combines a self-super supervised learning model and a Bayesian ensemble classification is proposed which outperforms the state-of-the-art models in recall and f1-score values by 20%.

## A Fine-grained citation graph for biomedical academic papers: the finding-citation graph

](/paper/A-Fine-grained-citation-graph-for-biomedical-the-Liang-Poesio/f184a04161434fc1c3b1a6e2eb9f6978e5bc3a7f)

[Yuan Liang](/author/Yuan-Liang/2315398654)[Massimo Poesio](/author/Massimo-Poesio/2315307448)[Roonak Rezvani](/author/Roonak-Rezvani/70864492)

Computer Science, Biology

-   2024

A richer form of citation graph with nodes for both academic papers and their findings: the finding-citation graph (FCG); a new pipeline to construct such a graph is presented, which includes a finding identification module and a citation sentence extraction module.

## Analysing behavioural changes in people with dementia using in‐home monitoring technologies

](/paper/Analysing-behavioural-changes-in-people-with-using-Rezvani-Kouchaki/b6a733b6aea6f4253c411851bf343c793784453c)

[Roonak Rezvani](/author/Roonak-Rezvani/70864492)[S. Kouchaki](/author/S.-Kouchaki/2481031)[R. Nilforooshan](/author/R.-Nilforooshan/5195508)[D. Sharp](/author/D.-Sharp/1879253179)[P. Barnaghi](/author/P.-Barnaghi/1740880)

Medicine

-   1 December 2021

A digital platform and analytical methods are used to generate alerts when changes occur in the digital markers collected using in‐home sensing technologies (i.e., vital signs, environmental and activity data).

[

## D4.2 Large Scale IoT Crawling, Indexing and Ranking

](/paper/D4.2-Large-Scale-IoT-Crawling%2C-Indexing-and-Ranking-Parreira-Austria/a1c43aa55b400b7bec1853129577ec674f20b2d8)

[J. Parreira](/author/J.-Parreira/1764853)[Siemens AG Austria](/author/Siemens-AG-Austria/2289151275)[Pavel Smirnov](/author/Pavel-Smirnov/2289119264)[Juan A. Martinez OdinS](/author/Juan-A.-Martinez-OdinS/2289143979)[Roonak Rezvani](/author/Roonak-Rezvani/70864492)

Computer Science, Engineering

-   2019

This deliverable summarises the work of Tasks T4.3.2 and T4.3.1, to develop crawling and indexing mechanisms to support the discovery and search of IoT devices, services and data, as well as ranking methods for the selection of IoT resources.

[

## Enabling Context-Aware Search using Extracted Insights from IoT Data Streams

](/paper/Enabling-Context-Aware-Search-using-Extracted-from-Janeiko-Rezvani/d3836585a049534da8e0c5da946275f3ce7abb53)

[Valentinas Janeiko](/author/Valentinas-Janeiko/1492100767)[Roonak Rezvani](/author/Roonak-Rezvani/70864492) [P. Barnaghi](/author/P.-Barnaghi/1740880)

Computer Science, Environmental Science

-   15 April 2020

A search engine designed for indexing, searching and accessing urban sensory data and also pattern search functions that are enabled by a pattern analysis algorithm, supported by monitoring of data streams for changes in quality of information and remediation is described.
